    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Reverend William George Gepford (January 12, 1927) was born in Kansas City, Missouri. He received a degree in electrical engineering from Colorado State University, his B.D. from McCormick Theological Seminary, and his Masters of Education from the University of Colorado, and his Doctor of Science in Theology from the San Francisco Theological Seminary.</p>
      <p>In his efforts to increase understanding between the Christian and Islamic faiths, he has traveled extensively and held a variety of positions both in the United States and overseas. He currently maintains an office at the Littlefield Presbyterian Church in Dearborn, Michigan.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection consists of two series: Professional Papers and Visual Materials. These series document William Gepford's efforts to bridge the Muslim and Christian faiths, both within his own ministry as well as international efforts. These efforts include seminars, interfaith worship services, and international initiatives. The collection also documents his everyday activities with the Presbyterian Church and interaction with the Detroit community.</p>
    </scopecontent>
